(
<figureCitation id="88EF2A16FFB70615FECFABAB44EAD394" box="[342,424,1944,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–20" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1820,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,199,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1437,193,1800]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. FIGURES 15–16. Liriomyza carphephori spec. nov.; 15: male; 16: puparia. FIGURES 17–18: Liriomyza helianthi Spencer; 17: puparia; 18: male. FIGURES 19–20: Liriomyza polygalivora spec. nov.; 19: female; 20: puparia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612617/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) Yellow to orange-yellow; formed outside the mine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
